description:
Add @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) block that disables all animations and transitions. Accessibility baseline per Emil and ui-engineer rules.

## Changes
- Add at end of styles.css:
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    *, *::before, *::after {
      animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
      animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
      transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    }
  }

## Acceptance
- All animations stop when OS reduced-motion is enabled
- No animation still visible
- Standard pattern from emil-design-eng skill

Write session records to NDJSON files in flowtime/sessions/<date>.ndjson. Append-only — each session/completion appends a JSON line. Schema:
Session: {"type":"session","date":"...","start_time":"...","end_time":"...","duration_minutes":N,"bucket":"...","task_text":"...","notes":"..."}
Completion: {"type":"completion","date":"...","bucket":"...","task_text":"...","completed_at":"..."}
Hook into timer stop/expiry for sessions. Hook into checkbox toggle for completions.
